text:
I'm not even an hour in (I haven't watched much of the streams because they're very long, only watched compilations), already obviously it felt almost a bit frustrating, seeing someone play through the first beats of a Minecraft playthrough, a lot slower than you would do it. But then, I realised that I'm actually jealous of Gura. She's not a pro Minecraft Speed runner og anything like that, she's not min/maxing everything with how you play. She's just playing the game. I miss that. I miss just being immersed in the game and doing things at my own pace. Not quickly doing all the essential stuff, being actually scared of mobs even when they're far away, actually pondering how I'd get food and wondering if I should eat what I have or not yet instead of immediately running straight towards the mushrooms to make more than enough soup (as I would have done spawning into this world) .

Once you know the game very thoroughly, it stops feeling like you're playing a game, and more like you're just following routines. Like a robot, doing steps on sequence, not wasting any time, not wasting any resources.
